HEADWORD: phrenico-
<hw>phrenico-</hw></mhw> <pr>(fr⟦ecr⟧n- or fr⟦emac⟧n-)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>frh`n</grk>, <grk>freno`s</grk>, the
midriff, or diaphragm, the heart (as the seat of emotions), the
mind.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A combining form meaning, of or
pertaining to the diaphragm, the mind, or the brain; frenic.</def>
<au>Stedman.</au>⟦br⟧
